entry.title: [ios] Fix NTP Omnibox first defocus animation
entry.content:
When the user taps the unpinned fakebox to focus the omnibox, the NTP

scrolls up to pin the fakebox and then focuses. On defocus, the NTP

should scroll back down to the previous position. But that only worked

on the second defocus - the first time it would just snap back

without animation.



The issue was that a property used to control the timing was not given

the expected initial value, so the first animation was canceled

immediately and the scroll position was set back without animation, and

then the property would get set back to the expected initial value so

that the second animation would work.

entry.title: PDF Viewer: Perform Select All only in response to Ctrl+A
entry.content:
Currently, the PDF Viewer looks for "Ctrl" and "A' to determine if it

should perform a Select All command, where "Ctrl" is "Cmd" on macOS.

This will also incorrectly match other key combinations, like

Ctrl+Shift+A, which is the keyboard shortcut for Tab Search.



Fix this by adding a hasCtrlModifierOnly() utility function and using

that instead of the existing hasCtrlModifier() function. Audit other "A"

key handling in PDF Viewer code and consistently use

hasCtrlModifierOnly().



Bug: 1498522

entry.title: Remove OnDidProcessDisplayChanges from WiredDisplayMediaRouteProvider
entry.content:
This CL removes the OnDidProcessDisplayChanges() DisplayObserver

override from WiredDisplayMediaRouteProvider.



This is only used in ChromeOS Ash by DisplayManager and is not

supported on other platforms. Follow up work will move this

directly into DisplayManager for clients that require updates to

ChromeOS system level display state changes.



There should be no behavioral changes introduced with this CL as

DisplayManager will also call OnDisplayAdded / OnDisplayRemoved

/ OnDisplayMetricsChanged whenever OnDidProcessDisplayChanges is

called.

entry.content:
This is a reland of commit 75c6595ba8a9bceab2b4e718f0a81f73a33b923b



Changes since original:

Do not actually load baselines yet, since wdspec tests need to be

migrated first. The `mac12-arm64-rel` failure could not be

reproduced.



Original change's description:

> [wptrunner] Translate TestExpectations and baselines to metadata

>

> This change switches wptrunner from reading expectations from `.ini`

> metadata files to reading them from existing TestExpectation lines and

> `*-expected.txt`. This is done by patching `testloader.TestLoader`,

> which generates (approximately) equivalent `.ini` syntax trees entirely

> in memory, at runtime.

>

> To support [1], errors messages in baselines are also loaded into

> `expected-fail-message` keys to be checked wptrunner-side by

> Chrome-specific executors.

>

> Also, remove the `(INTERNAL|EXTERNAL)-*` wptrunner statuses, as `mozlog`

> will refuse to log them [2].

>

entry.title: [Remote Playback] Filter Compatible devices for video-only media content
entry.content:
This CL makes the media codec optional so that it's not required to have

a valid video and audio codec. A missing audio_codec is treated

differently from an invalid codec:

- if the Remote Playback source URL doesn't include the `audio_codec`

field, the Cast MRP won't check the receiver devices' audio capabilities.

- if the media content has an unknown codec, the Remote Playback URL

will include "audio_codec=unknown" and no devices will be compatible.



Note that this change only affects the Remote Playback API

implementation. For Remote Playback Media Source initialized for Media

Remoting from Zenith, it is guaranteed that the source URL contains an

`audio_codec` field because media content without audio track

won't be shown in Zenith.

entry.title: Perf: Improve ergonomics: --fetch-data-path-local
entry.content:
Currently many non-Android (e.g. Linux, Windows, Mac) generate and copy

over *.profraw to the current working directory by default. Thus they

are able to use the args in

https://chromium.googlesource.com/chromium/src/+/main/docs/pgo.md pretty

much as is.



On Android, there are many additional args that are hard to get right.

One of these is --fetch-data-path-local which is actually used in the

code as options.local_data_path, and it's not used on the bots since

bots set ISOLATED_OUTDIR, making it doubly hard to discover and use

correctly.



This CL sets the default for --fetch-data-path-local to be the current

working directory, when ISOLATED_OUTDIR is not defined, to match the

default behaviour for other non-Android platforms. This should also not

affect bots since they set ISOLATED_OUTDIR.

entry.title: content/cc: Safely drop stale callbacks with RenderDocument + CC reuse
entry.content:
Since LayerTreeHost is threaded, callbacks tied to a frame submitted by

the main thread are posted asynchronously. This means when the

compositor is swapped between widgets (for RenderDocument), the new

widget could receive callbacks tied to content submitted by the

previous widget resulting in errors.



This change avoids this by adding a source_frame_number to such

callbacks. The source_frame_number is 1:1 with main frames and as such

can be used to tie callbacks to a particular frame. The LayerTreeView

can then safely ignore callbacks for main frames submitted by a

previous widget.

entry.title: [omnibox][cr23] Fix action chip color for high-contrast / themed clients
entry.content:
In addition to those clients who are eligible for the full CR2023 color

treatment, there exists a subset of clients who are not eligible for the

CR2023 colors even though they have enabled the ChromeRefresh2023 flag.

In particular, those clients who utilize high-contrast mode and/or a

custom theme will not be eligible for the usual CR2023 color mappings.



This CL introduces a set of color tokens and mappings which will ensure

that all clients are presented with reasonable colors for the action

chip irrespective of whether or not they're using high-contrast mode

and/or a custom theme. Without this fix, the action chip renders in an

opaque black (or white) color when the user attempts to hover/select it.



As noted below, this CL will only affect clients who enable CR2023 and

are using high-contrast mode and/or a custom theme. All other clients

will remain unaffected by the changes in this CL.

entry.title: Workaround for 3PCB when rendering sandboxed media
entry.content:
When 3PCB is enabled, access-controlled media URLs that

are served with "Content-Security-Policy: sandbox" will be

broken when it is loaded as the top-level URL.



This includes static media types where there is little privacy

or security risk to allowing cookies to be send for the data

request when the media is being loaded as the top-level document.



The CL patches this by overriding Document::SiteForCookies in these

specific cases. To be cautious, this is only done in the

MediaDocumentParser.
